# ANGULAR OPEN LIBRARY APP - COMPLETE IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE
## For AI Agent - Step-by-Step Instructions

This guide provides complete, production-ready code for building an award-winning Open Library search application using Angular 16+ and Tailwind CSS 3.

---

## SECTION 1: PROJECT SETUP & CONFIGURATION

### Step 1.1: Create Angular Project
```bash
ng new open-library-app
cd open-library-app
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p
```

### Step 1.2: Configure Tailwind CSS
**File: `tailwind.config.js`**
```javascript
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/**/*.{html,ts}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: '#0f172a',
        secondary: '#1e293b',
        accent: '#3b82f6',
        'accent-dark': '#1e40af',
      },
      animation: {
        'fade-in': 'fadeIn 0.6s ease-in',
        'slide-up': 'slideUp 0.8s ease-out',
        'pulse-soft': 'pulseSoft 2s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.6, 1) infinite',
      },
      keyframes: {
        fadeIn: {
          '0%': { opacity: '0' },
          '100%': { opacity: '1' },
        },
        slideUp: {
          '0%': { transform: 'translateY(30px)', opacity: '0' },
          '100%': { transform: 'translateY(0)', opacity: '1' },
        },
        pulseSoft: {
          '0%, 100%': { opacity: '1' },
          '50%': { opacity: '0.7' },
        },
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

